Which of the following is a POWER7 workload-optimizing feature?
A. FFDC
B. ASMI
C. MinCore
D. TurboCore
Answer: D
Reference:http://public.dhe.ibm.com/partnerworld/pub/whitepaper/193e6.pdf(page 18)
Which tool can be used in the sizing process to provide templates for workloads?
A. WLE
B. TDA
C. SPT
D. PM for Power Systems
Answer: C
Which statement for IBM POWER7 EnergyScale Enhancements is true?
A. Smart Fan Control regulates fan speeds based on CPU workload.
B. TPMD will allow POWER7 cores to "Over clock" if workload demands are present.
C. TPMD Hardware is part of the base hardware configuration for enterprise servers only.
D. Express servers need to be plugged into an IPDU extract power consumption, inlet and
exhaust temperature data.
Answer: B
Reference:https://www-
950.ibm.com/events/wwe/ca/canada.nsf/vLookupPDFs/Power7_presentation/$file/Power7_
presentation.pdf(slide 93)

What is an expected output in the process of sizing a new system for a customer?
A. Storage space requirements
B. Expected hardwarerequirements
C. Expected growth in data size

Answer: C
If a customer wanted to change the Integrated Virtual Ethernet adapter (IVE) currently
installed in their Power 710 or Power 730 server, which option is valid?
A. Order a different one later with MES order
B. Use DLPAR and add the new card to the server.
C. Run the AIX "rmdev" command, followed by the "cfgmgr" command.
D. The card is hot-swap, so they could remove the current card and replace it with their
new choice without powering down the server.
Answer: C
